```java
public class DailySchedule {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Define your preferred wake-up time
        String wakeUpTime = "7:00 AM";

        // Create an array to hold your daily activities
        String[][] schedule = {
            {"7:00 AM", "Wake-up"},
            {"7:30 AM", "Breakfast"},
            {"8:00 AM", "Workout"},
            {"9:00 AM", "Bath and freshen up"},
            {"9:30 AM", "Study or Work"},
            {"12:30 PM", "Lunch"},
            {"1:30 PM", "Study or Work"},
            {"5:30 PM", "Finish Work/Study"},
            {"6:00 PM", "Leisure time"},
            {"8:00 PM", "Dinner"},
            {"9:00 PM", "Free time or Relaxation"},
            {"10:30 PM", "Unwind and prepare for bed"},
            {"11:00 PM", "Sleep"}};

        // Create a stack to hold your schedule for two days
        Stack<String[]> scheduleStack = new Stack<>();
        scheduleStack.push(schedule); // Add the first day's schedule to the stack

        // Iterate over the stack for two days
        for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
            // How many days you want to display the schedule
            if (i == 1) {
                System.out.println("Daily Schedule for Day 1:");
            } else if (i == 2) {
                System.out.println("Daily Schedule for Day 2:");
            } else {
                System.out.println("Daily Schedule for Day 3:");
            }

            // Display the schedule
            while (!scheduleStack.isEmpty()) {
                String[] scheduleData = scheduleStack.pop();
                for (String activity : scheduleData) {
                    System.out.println(wakeUpTime + " - " + activity);
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```
This program will output a schedule for three days, with each day's schedule being displayed when the program runs. Each day's schedule is stored in an array of strings, where the time is the first element and the activity is the second element. The schedule is displayed in reverse order, as it is being removed from a stack. You can customize this code to add or remove activities, change the times, or adjust the schedule for your specific needs.

